<head>
<title> Visigothic Music / bauhaus / Dark Entries </title>
<base href="http://olivier.dementia.org/~visigoth/music/bauhaus/">
<link rel="made" href="../../visigoth.html">
<link rel="up" href="../index.html">
</head>

<body>

<fig align=center src="../../V.gif">
<center> <img src="../../V.gif" alt="V"> </center>
</fig>

<hr>

<h1>bauhaus <br> ``Dark Entries''</h1>

<blockquote>
Caressing bent up to the jug again<br>
With sheaths and pills<br>
Invading all those stills<br>
In a hovel of a bed<br>
I will scream in pain<br>
Oh please, miss lane<br>
Leave me with some pain<br>
Went walking through this city's neon lights<br>
In fear of disguising my warping seething<br>
Pressure lines and graceless heirs<br>
Intangible of price<br>
Trying so hard to fine what? what was right<br>
I came upon your room it stuck into my head<br>
We leapt into the bed degrading even lice<br>
You took delight in taking down<br>
All my shielded pride<br>
Until exposed became my darker side<br>
Puckering up and down some avenue of sin<br>
Too cheap to ride they're woth a try<br>
If only for the old times, cold times<br>
Don't go waving your pretentious love<br>
He's soliciting on his tan brown brogues<br>
Gyrating through some lonesome devil's row<br>
Pinpointing well meaning upper class prey<br>
Of walking money check possessing holes<br>
He often sleekly offers his services<br>
Exploitation of his finer years<br>
Work with loosely woven fabrics<br>
Of lonely office clerks<br>
Any lay suffices his dollar green eye
</blockquote>

<hr>

