<h1>Subscription Information</h1>
</center>

<p> <center> <img src="graphics/sep.jpg" alt="------------------------------">
</center>

<blockquote>

<p>To subscribe to the normal fight-censorship mailing list, send a
"subscribe" request in the body of a message addressed to:

<center><p>fight-censorship-request@andrew.cmu.edu</center>

<hr>

<p>To subscribe to fight-censorship-digest, send the command:

<center><p>subscribe fight-censorship-digest</center>

<p>in the body of a message to "Majordomo@vorlon.mit.edu".  If you want
to subscribe something other than the account the mail is coming from,
such as a local redistribution list, then append that address to the
"subscribe" command; for example, to subscribe "local-fight-censorship":

<center><p>subscribe fight-censorship-digest local-fight-censorship@your.domain.net</center>

<p>The fight-censorship list is run by <a
href=mailto:declan@well.com>Declan McCullagh, who is a plaintiff in
the ACLU/EFF lawsuit challenging the Communications Decency Act. For
more information, take a look at the <a
href="http://fight-censorship.dementia.org/top/">complete list
archives.</a>


</blockquote>

