Eric Adler of the Kansas City Star caught some less-covered moments from
the Olympics.  Including this one:

	Foreign journalists getting pepper spray in the face as they
	tried to enter their offices after the Olympic Park bombing.
	Police wanted to secure the building. Reporters wanted to file
	stories. Struck by the spray, some journalists fell to their knees, 
	vomiting.


http://www.kcstar.com/news/stories/moments.htm


