Folks, I apologize for the mail problems. I still haven't quite figured 
out exactly what happened -- I'm not at home, but in NYC on business, so 
I wasn't able to log on this evening until now.

Seems as though the problem happened when I forwarded a fight-censorship
message to cypherpunks, which has among its subscribers a nonexistent
address at axcess.net.in. For some reason, a poorly-configured machine at
axcess.net.in started repeatedly resending the forwarded message back to
fight-censorship. Odd. I think I've blocked it from doing it again. 

I blame the problem on AOL, of course.

On a topic more germane to the list, I was in Times Square with Glenn and
some NYC webperns this evening, having dinner in a delightful greasy
burger joint. For no apparent reason, a woman sitting next to me started
to describe, in painstaking detail, how to kill someone with a hatpin. (A
jab to the nerve center in the solar plexus, if you must know.)

I started to think to myself, especially after Dara's note earlier, that 
this kind of material should be banned! Censor biology texts on the Net!

Yours in protecting children from dangerous knowledge,

Declan


