Found this buried deep in the long version of an AP story about the
Atlanta pipe bomb suspect:

      Bomb-making instructions available through the global computer
      network have contributed to an increase in bombings in the United
      States, authorities say. 

Did I miss the news story where that contribution was identified?  Or is 
the AP mis-stating what their FBI "expert" said on Monday.

Incidentally, the source for the oft-repeated statement that the FBI was 
"trying to determine whether Jewell may have had access to the campus
Internet" [sic] is not in the FBI; it's someone on the campus who believes
that that's what the FBI is doing.

