I talked to Trueman today.

He told me Shea's victory was "not unexpected."

"The ACLU did some forum shopping. If I were going to file a suit like they
did, I'd go to Manhattan," he said, adding that NYC is much more permissive
than most parts of the country.

When I told him that Shea rather strongly dislikes the ACLU and refused to
join the ACLU lawsuit, Trueman was incredulous. Said that Shea must have
received some help from the ACLU in preparing briefs or whatnot.

Not quite.

-Declan



