	For the record, we didn't forum-shop.  Also, I don't strongly
dislike the ACLU, and I certainly agree with them on the CDA.  Finally,
our case landed in NY because the correspondent firm that was going to
handle the case here backed out at the last moment -- on Feb. 7, the night
before we filed.  Our judges were relatively conservative.  We were not
assoisted by the ACLU, with whom we had a short-lived feud.

