 [None of the below is really on-topic for fight-censorship, but because
 Lemire posed specific questions here, I'll answer them here. 

 As far as the topic of fight-censorship goes, Marc Lemire strongly
 disagrees with Sol Littman's campaign to shut down his web site, and so do
 the Nizkor folks and I. Obviously, we disagree concerning the value and
 importance of the content of Mr. Lemire's web pages, but that's a matter of
 free speech -- in other, more appropriate forums.

 If anyone wishes to pursue these off-topic issues, please cross-post to
 alt.fan.ernst-zundel. I no longer read alt.revisionism; not really my
 forte, and I'm too busy with other things.]

On Wed, 31 Jul 1996, Marc Lemire wrote:

&gt; &gt;You covered the wrong web site. People are actually more "concerned" about
&gt; &gt;the skinheads site, http://www.ftcnet.com/~skinhds/main.htm. Lemire's is
&gt; &gt;pretty inoffensive, basically just a collection of obvious neo-Nazi front
