     The Communications Decency Amendment (CDA) Country-Wide Protest

                         August 31, 1996


In order to protest the Communications Decency Amendment (CDA) of the 1996
Telecommunications Act, on August 31, 1996 everyone who is against the 2
acts, and believes that these acts are unconstitutional, are asked to
drive with their lights on during the daytime.

Please forward this message to all newspapers, t.v. stations, and if you
have a internet site, please display this message.  The more participation
we have, the more our message gets across!

[This is a grassroots campaign, not tied to any particular organization.]



